result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 15CM-301, 15CM-402 and 15TR-1970 - All Cases Called @ 3:29 PM: Defendant Victoria Gomez in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Enrique Soria present as Interpreter.  Oath administered at previous hearing today.  Global resolution recited by DA.  Def and counsel concur with State's recital.  15CM-402:  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. 15CM-402 Plea Ct 1:  GP  Plea Ct 2:  GP  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  15CM-301 and 15TR-1970 - Both DRI.  Argument by DA as to penalty - joint recommendation however, any further offenses will result in the State arguing for potential jail time being imposed..  No statement by SPD.  No statement offered by Def.  The Court:  Ct 1 Court Costs imposed plus DNA surcharge.  Ct 2 $200 fine plus costs of DNA surcharge.  Sample to be provided today.  Expungement process through the DOJ explained.  Hispanic Appeal Rights Given.
No operation of any motor vehicles.

Case Called @ 3:00 PM: Defendant Victoria Gomez in court.  Marc A Bickford appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Enrique Soria present as Interpreter.  Oath administered at previous hearing today.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def wants counsel.  She is employed Full Time.  Upon discussion of earnings, Def referred to SPD for eligibility.   NGP entered by Court.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Status conference scheduled for September 8, 2015 at 03:45 pm.
